      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(lmstudio): pass configured contextWindow to embedding model preload",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- **Problem**: LM Studio embedding preload calls `ensureLmstudioModelLoaded` without `requestedContextLength`, causing LM Studio to load models with the maximum supported context length (32K). On GPUs with limited VRAM this triggers CUDA OOM.\n- **Root cause**: The embedding provider path in `createLmstudioEmbeddingProvider` omitted `requestedContextLength` from the `ensureLmstudioModelLoaded` call, unlike the inference path which resolves it via `resolveRequestedContextLength`.\n- **Fix**: Resolve `requestedContextLength` from the model config (`contextTokens` → `contextWindow`) with provider-level fallback, and pass it to `ensureLmstudioModelLoaded`.\n- **What did NOT change**: Inference path untouched. No new exported functions. No changes to the load helper.\n\nCloses #97016\n\n## Change Type\n\n- [x] Bug fix\n\n## Scope\n\n- [x] Extension (LM Studio provider)\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** `createLmstudioEmbeddingProvider` now resolves `requestedContextLength` from model-level or provider-level config and passes it to `ensureLmstudioModelLoaded`.\n\n**Environment tested:** Node 24.13.1 on Linux, `node --import tsx` calling real `asPositiveSafeInteger` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/string-coerce-runtime`.\n\n**Before fix (main @ 80c754d):**\n\nThe embedding provider call omits `requestedContextLength`:\n\n```text\nextensions/lmstudio/src/embedding-provider.ts:124:\n    await ensureLmstudioModelLoaded({\n      baseUrl,\n      apiKey,\n      headers: headerOverrides,\n      ssrfPolicy,\n      modelKey: model,\n      timeoutMs: 120_000,\n      // ❌ requestedContextLength NOT passed — defaults to 64000\n    });\n```\n\n**After fix (this branch):**\n\nThe embedding provider resolves and passes `requestedContextLength`:\n\n```text\nextensions/lmstudio/src/embedding-provider.ts:128:\n  const requestedContextLength =\n    asPositiveSafeInteger(modelConfig?.contextTokens) ??\n    asPositiveSafeInteger(modelConfig?.contextWindow) ??\n    asPositiveSafeInteger(providerConfig?.contextTokens) ??\n    asPositiveSafeInteger(providerConfig?.contextWindow);\n...\n    await ensureLmstudioModelLoaded({\n      ...\n      requestedContextLength,  // ✅ passes configured context length\n    });\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix — context length resolution:**\n\n```text\n$ node --import tsx --no-warnings proof-97016.mjs\nmodel contextWindow=8192 → 8192\nmodel contextTokens=4096 (over contextWindow=32768) → 4096\nprovider contextWindow=16384 → 16384\nprovider contextTokens=2048 → 2048\nno config → undefined\n\n✅ All assertions passed\n```\n\n**Observed result after the fix:** The configured `contextWindow` (e.g. 8192) is now resolved and passed as `requestedContextLength`, so LM Studio loads with the user-configured context length instead of the model maximum. Existing tests: 98/98 passed.\n\n**Not tested:** Live LM Studio with CUDA GPU. Verified via real production SDK function (`asPositiveSafeInteger`) and resolution precedence logic matching the inference path's `resolveRequestedContextLength`.\n\n## Security Impact\n\n- New permissions? No\n- Secrets handling changed? No\n- New network calls? No\n",
        "branch": "fix/97016-lmstudio-embedding-context-window",
